hkl
------------------------------------------
The hkl library is a framework for diffraction computation and diffractometer
control, heavily used at the SOLEIL synchrotron. It supports various types of
diffractometer geometry: Eulerian 4-circle, Eulerian 6-circle, kappa 4-circle,
kappa 6-circle, and z-axis geometry. For each of these it provides several
numerically computed modes, such as bisector and constant psi.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.10.0-1
  libglib2.0-devel-2.54.3-1
  libglib2.0_0-2.54.3-1
  libgsl-devel-2.3-2
  libgsl19-2.3-2
  libgtk2.0_0-2.24.32-1
  libhkl-devel-5.0.0.2449-1bl1
  libhkl5-5.0.0.2449-1bl1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.31.0-1
  gcc-core-6.4.0-5
  gcc-g++-6.4.0-5
  gobject-introspection-1.54.1-1
  libtool-2.4.6-5
  make-4.2.1-2
  python-2.7.14-1

Canonical website:
  http://www.synchrotron-soleil.fr/portal/page/portal/Instrumentation/EnvironnementInstrumental/hkl

Canonical download:
  mirror://debian/pool/main/h/hkl/hkl_5.0.0.2449.orig.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack hkl-5.0.0.2449-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./hkl-5.0.0.2449-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/hkl-5.0.0.2449-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/hkl-5.0.0.2449-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libhkl5-5.0.0.2449-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libhkl-devel-5.0.0.2449-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/girepository-Hkl5.0-5.0.0.2449-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(hkl)
  /usr/bin/ghkl.exe
  /usr/share/applications/ghkl.desktop
